The Telegraph - Calcutta : Frontpage
 Saturday, July 03, 2004 				 Ministry report
																								New Delhi, July 2: Dhananjoy Chatterjee appears all but steps away from the gallows.																								The Union home ministry today sent its report to President A.P.J. Abdul Kalam, making a strong case for turning down Dhananjoys second mercy plea. Kalam is expected to go by the home ministrys advice and formally clear the way for execution of the death penalty.Dhananjoy was scheduled to be sent to the gallows on June 25. The home ministry, however, had asked the jail authorities in Bengal to put the execution on hold as the President was yet to dispose of a mercy plea from Dhananjoys family.
